    - "itertools classes are implemented in C. For C-implemented types, __qualname__ == __name__ (no enclosing class or function scope). All 8 classes checked share this property; verified with Python 3.14.3."
    - "itertools.count.__qualname__ == 'count'; itertools.cycle.__qualname__ == 'cycle'; itertools.repeat.__qualname__ == 'repeat'; all verified with Python 3.14.3."
    - "itertools.chain.__qualname__ == 'chain'; itertools.islice.__qualname__ == 'islice'; itertools.groupby.__qualname__ == 'groupby'; all verified with Python 3.14.3."
    - "itertools.product.__qualname__ == 'product'; itertools.accumulate.__qualname__ == 'accumulate'; both verified with Python 3.14.3."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
  created_at: "2026-04-11T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

